## Proactive Behaviors - Do These Without Being Asked

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Opening any project for the first time | Check if `graphify-out/graph.json` exists. If not, run `graphify build`. Check if GitNexus indexed. |
| About to read source files to understand code | Query graphify first: `graphify query "q" --graph "[GRAPH_PATH]"` |
| User pastes a URL and asks anything about it | YouTube: yt-dlp + fabric. Web: `curl -sL URL \| fabric -p summarize` |
| Non-text file appears (PDF, docx, xlsx, image) | Run `markitdown <file>` before reading |
| About to say "done", "fixed", "complete", "it works" | Run verification-before-completion first. Evidence before claims, always. |
| Completed a meaningful feature or fix | Log to vault immediately |
| About to do anything expensive (large agent run, many files) | Run `codeburn status` first to check burn rate |
| Session is getting long or context is filling | Run handoff skill to create a carry-forward doc |
| API key needed for a project | Check `~/.claude/api-keys.json` first. If not there, ask. |
| New code being written | Apply karpathy-guidelines mentally: state assumptions, prefer simple, surgical changes only |
| Session starts | Check `~/.claude/claude-queue/queue.json` - if items pending, process them |

