## Auto-Invoke Skills - MANDATORY. Detect -> invoke -> act. No slash command needed.

**FULL AUTONOMY:** Every skill is available at all times without slash commands or explicit permission. If a skill improves output, use it. If a tool verifies something, use it. Act on best judgment, report what was done.

### Planning and Design (fires BEFORE any implementation)

**brainstorming** - invoke when:
- "I want to add X", "build me Y", "can we do Z" - any new feature, component, or capability
- "What should I do about X" - open-ended decisions
- "How should I approach this"
- Do NOT invoke for: typo fixes, config tweaks, single-line changes, already-fully-specified tasks

**writing-plans** - invoke when:
- Task will touch more than 3 files or take more than 20 minutes
- "Plan this out", "let us think through this"
- Complexity is not clear and mapping is needed before acting

**prototype** - invoke when:
- "Let me see what this would look like", "prototype this", "quick mockup"
- Routes: logic question -> terminal prototype; visual question -> multi-variation UI

---

### UI and Frontend (fires BEFORE writing any code)
# Remove this section if you do not do frontend work

**ui-ux-pro-max** - invoke when:
- Any React component, JSX, CSS, Tailwind, Electron renderer work
- "Make this look better", "redesign", "add a card", "style this"
- Do NOT invoke for: backend logic, scripts, CLI tools

**design-motion-principles** - invoke when:
- Adding hover states, transitions, animations, micro-interactions
- "This feels sluggish", "animate this", "add some life to it"
- Do NOT invoke for: static layouts with no motion

**impeccable** - invoke when:
- UI needs to go from functional to polished
- "Make it better", "improve the design", "this looks bland"
- Polish pass after initial implementation

**frontend-design** - invoke when:
- Building a full page or view (not just a small component tweak)
- Need layout + component architecture + visual design together

---

### Debugging and Quality

**systematic-debugging** - invoke when:
- Any error, exception, crash, or unexpected output
- "This is not working", "why is X happening", "something broke"
- Do NOT invoke for: planned refactors with no error present

**verification-before-completion** - invoke before EVERY completion claim:
- Run the actual command, see actual output, then report
- Iron law: never say "done" without evidence

**triage** - invoke when:
- Multiple bugs exist and priority is not clear
- "What should I fix first", incoming issue list needs ordering

---

### Execution and Delivery

**executing-plans** - invoke when a plan exists and it is time to run it

**dispatching-parallel-agents** + **subagent-driven-development** - invoke when:
- 3+ independent tasks can run simultaneously
- Large feature requiring multiple files across different areas
- Do NOT invoke for: tasks that must be sequential

**finishing-a-development-branch** - invoke when:
- Implementation complete, tests pass
- "Wrap this up", "how do I ship this"

