## AI Model Routing - MANDATORY

Before spending Sonnet/Opus credits, check if this task belongs to a cheaper model.

| Task | Model | How |
|------|-------|-----|
| Summarize a file | Gemini 2.5 Flash | `llm -m gemini-2.5-flash "summarize" < file.txt` |
| Explain a short code snippet | Gemini 2.5 Flash | pipe snippet |
| Generate a regex or query | Gemini 2.5 Flash | prompt directly |
| Draft vault notes (known topic) | Gemini 2.5 Flash | prompt directly |
| Quick data transform | Gemini 2.5 Flash | `cat file.txt \| llm -m gemini-2.5-flash "convert to JSON"` |
| Write tests for trivial code | Gemini 2.5 Flash | pipe the file |
| Codebase Q&A | graphify query | never raw Sonnet file reads |
| Multi-file code changes | Claude Sonnet | current session - justified |
| Complex debugging | Claude Sonnet | only after graphify query fails |
| Architecture decisions | Claude Sonnet | |
| Novel unsolved problems | Claude Opus | only if Sonnet fails twice |

### Routing rules
1. File reading for summarization -> always pipe through llm -m gemini-2.5-flash first; only escalate to Sonnet if output is insufficient
2. Never use Sonnet to: summarize files, generate simple patterns, format data, explain already-visible code
3. Graphify queries use Gemini automatically when GEMINI_API_KEY is set in env

